---
title: "Sequence of Events in the Simulation Engine Relating the Manure Module to the Other Modules"
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant S as SimulationEngine
    participant N as Non-Manure Modules
    participant M as Manure Module
    participant MM as ManureManagement
    participant MSC as Manure Subcomponents

    activate S
    loop Every day of simulation
        S->>N: calls daily_animal_routine() on animal module
        S->>M: calls simulate_daily_manure_management() on manure module
        deactivate S
        activate M
        M->>MM: calls daily_update() manure management
        deactivate M

        activate MM
        loop Every animal pen
            MM->>MSC: creates a manure management pen
            MM->>MSC: calls daily_update() on a manure handler
            MM->>MSC: calls daily_update() on a reception pit
            opt is a pre-separator digester present?
                MM->>MSC: calls daily_update() on an anaerobic digester
            end

            opt is a manure separator present?
                MM->>MSC: calls daily_update() on a manure separator
            end

            opt is a post-separator digester present?
                MM->>MSC: calls daily_update() on an anaerobic digester
            end

            MM->>MSC: calls daily_update() on a manure treatment
            MM->>MSC: appends daily output data
        end

        opt is last day of simulation?
            MM->>MSC: exports data and produces graphics
        end

        deactivate MM
        activate S
        S->>N: calls daily_fields_routine() on soil and crop module
        S->>N: calls daily_feed_routine() on feed module
        S->>N: calls daily_update() on output handler
    end
    deactivate S